HEADWORD: Thrummy
<hw>Thrum"my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like thrums; made of,
furnished with, or characterized by, thrums.</def>
<rj><au>Dampier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On her head <qex>thrummy</qex> cap she had.</q>
<rj><qau>Chalkhill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrumwort</ent>⟦br⟧
